with content_updates(module_slug, section_slug, body) as (
  values
    ('forging-your-destiny-introduction', 'welcome-warriors-code', $body$Renegade Millionaire is a time-management, productivity, goal-setting, and personal-development system built around clarity, discipline, and execution. The opening standard is simple: focus is a weapon, and distraction is the enemy.

This program is not passive education. It is built to convert insight into daily action, repeated habits, and measurable progress. The work only matters when it is applied.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-introduction', 'applied-knowledge', $body$The trap is saying "I know that" while failing to live it. Knowledge that is not applied does not change outcomes, habits, money, relationships, or identity.

Use this section as an honesty check. Identify where you already know the right move but have not yet installed the discipline to execute it.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-introduction', 'future-created-today', $body$Your future is not created by a single breakthrough. It is created through daily choices, repeated actions, and the standards you refuse to compromise.

Every module builds on that principle. Vision becomes goals, goals become mission, mission becomes time command, and time command becomes daily execution.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-introduction', 'program-layout', $body$The course moves in sequence for a reason. Module 1 establishes vision and the WARRIOR Map. Module 2 turns dreams into measurable goals. Module 3 creates visible Mission Briefs to keep priorities in front of you daily.

The later modules define mission, break goals into tactical plans, master time, build high performance, install the Battle Report, reinforce discipline rituals, and program the Warrior's Creed. The progression moves from clarity to planning to execution to identity reinforcement.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-introduction', 'course-commitment', $body$Before moving forward, make a clear commitment to execution. The program will ask you to write, decide, review, and act. Skipping the work means keeping the same life patterns.

Commit to completing the exercises, reviewing your answers, and taking immediate action from each module.$body$),

    ('warriors-vision-commanding-your-future', 'importance-of-goal-setting', $body$Goals are non-negotiable for anyone who wants command over his future. Without goals, a man reacts to noise, urgency, and distraction. With goals, he gains clarity, motivation, accountability, and a way to measure progress.

The operating principle is this: define victory first, then work backward into action. Goal setting is not a soft exercise. It is the starting point for leadership, discipline, and self-command.$body$),
    ('warriors-vision-commanding-your-future', 'defining-your-battlefield', $body$Vision is a clear picture of what victory looks like across life. It governs your mission, discipline, decisions, and legacy. Without vision, distractions choose your battles for you.

Your battlefield includes your body, habits, wealth, relationships, identity, work, and spiritual resolve. When each area is named clearly, you can choose battles deliberately instead of drifting through them.$body$),
    ('warriors-vision-commanding-your-future', 'vision-mapping-drill', $body$The Vision Mapping Drill turns vague ambition into a vivid future. Imagine your life at its peak and describe the physical strength, routines, occupation, spiritual alignment, brotherhood, wealth, and legacy you are building.

Write in practical detail. The clearer the picture, the easier it becomes to reverse-engineer goals and actions in the next modules.$body$),
    ('warriors-vision-commanding-your-future', 'dream-life-immersion', $body$Dream Life Immersion asks you to step into the future before you have built it. Describe where you live, who stands beside you, how you lead, how you serve, and what your days look like.

The purpose is not fantasy. The purpose is specificity. A warrior cannot attack a foggy target.$body$),
    ('warriors-vision-commanding-your-future', 'big-domino', $body$The Big Domino is the one goal, action, or decision that creates a chain reaction and makes other goals easier or unnecessary. It protects you from confusing busyness with progress.

Review your vision and identify the highest-impact objective. If an action moves the Big Domino, prioritize it. If it does not, eliminate it, defer it, or delegate it.$body$),
    ('warriors-vision-commanding-your-future', 'warrior-map', $body$The WARRIOR Map is your life command center. Warfare covers physical and mental health. Arsenal covers habits and routines. Riches covers wealth. Relationships covers brotherhood and connection. Identity and Purpose covers meaning and legacy. Occupation covers work and impact. Resolve covers spiritual strength and faith.

Rate each area honestly. Then identify the strongest zones, the weakest zones, and the one or two areas that need immediate action.$body$),
    ('warriors-vision-commanding-your-future', 'next-3-major-goals', $body$The WARRIOR Goal System demands precision. Goals must be specific, aligned with mission, demanding but achievable, measurable, time-bound, resistant to obstacles, and supported by daily execution.

Forge three major goals for the next 12 months. For each goal, define the exact target, daily and weekly actions, likely obstacles, and counterattacks.$body$),
    ('warriors-vision-commanding-your-future', 'warrior-declaration', $body$Goal setting is only useful when paired with the mindset required to finish. Motivation fades. Discipline carries the mission when feelings shift.

Write a declaration that commits you to action, adaptation, and persistence. This is your standard when resistance appears.$body$),
    ('warriors-vision-commanding-your-future', 'recap-reflection', $body$You should now have a clear life vision, an honest WARRIOR Map assessment, three high-impact goals, and a commitment statement.

Review what clarity has revealed. Notice what excites you, what challenges you, and what must change immediately.$body$),

    ('forging-your-destiny-from-dreams-to-reality', 'from-vision-to-action', $body$Vision without action remains fantasy. Goals are the bridge between the future you described and the daily behavior that will create it.

This module converts dreams into specific, categorized goals. Each goal needs a clear target, a timeline, and a place inside the WARRIOR framework.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-from-dreams-to-reality', 'dreams-to-actionable-goals', $body$Rewrite each dream from Module 1 as a concrete goal. Define what the target is, when it will be achieved, and which WARRIOR category it belongs to.

The outcome is a usable list of objectives instead of broad wishes. Precision makes planning possible.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-from-dreams-to-reality', 'top-3-goals', $body$Now narrow your goals into the three highest-impact missions. These are your Big Dominos: the goals that create progress across multiple areas and reduce scattered effort.

For each top goal, define the outcome, deadline, top ten actions, progress measure, resources, celebration plan, and final positive goal statement.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-from-dreams-to-reality', 'discovering-your-why', $body$Goals alone are not enough. You need a deep emotional reason to persist when motivation fades, fatigue appears, or obstacles hit.

Your why turns a goal from a preference into a commitment. The stronger the emotional reason, the harder it becomes to quit.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-from-dreams-to-reality', '100-reasons-why', $body$List the reasons you must achieve each top goal. Surface-level reasons will not be enough when pressure rises, so keep digging until the mission feels personal and unavoidable.

Use the list as fuel. Review it when resistance, distraction, or doubt shows up.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-from-dreams-to-reality', '100-consequences', $body$Facing consequences creates urgency. Write what happens if you do not act, if you stay the same, and if the goal remains unfinished.

This is not negative thinking. It is honest cost assessment. A warrior counts the cost of inaction as clearly as the reward of victory.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-from-dreams-to-reality', 'persistence-willpower', $body$Persistence separates people who talk from people who finish. Obstacles, setbacks, and pressure are expected parts of the path, not signs to quit.

Persistence can be trained through definiteness of purpose, desire, self-reliance, clear plans, accurate knowledge, cooperation, willpower, and habit.$body$),
    ('forging-your-destiny-from-dreams-to-reality', 'recap-reflection', $body$You have converted dreams into measurable goals, chosen your Top 3 Big Dominos, identified deeper reasons for success, and faced the cost of failure.

Before moving on, choose the goal you are most excited to complete and the next concrete action that proves you are serious.$body$),

    ('warriors-battle-cards-mission-brief', 'why-mission-brief', $body$The Mission Brief is the reinforcement layer after vision and goal planning. It turns goals into a visible, structured, battle-ready reminder of what must be executed daily.

This is more than a goal card. It is an order for execution, designed to keep the target unavoidable and prevent distraction from pulling you off course.$body$),
    ('warriors-battle-cards-mission-brief', 'create-mission-brief', $body$Build the Mission Brief as a physical or digital tool that is tangible, visible, emotionally charged, and easy to review every day.

The brief needs four core parts: an inspiring visual, a precise measurable goal, a hard deadline, and a Statement of Victory written in completed form.$body$),
    ('warriors-battle-cards-mission-brief', 'use-mission-brief', $body$Keep the Mission Brief close. Read it morning and night. Visualize the result as already achieved. Return to it whenever doubt, fatigue, or distraction appears.

The brief works because it keeps your mission in your environment and in your language every day.$body$),
    ('warriors-battle-cards-mission-brief', 'statement-of-desire', $body$The Statement of Desire names what you want, when it will be achieved, what you are willing to give, and why the mission matters.

It should focus on one mission at a time and remove ambiguity. A vague desire cannot command disciplined action.$body$),
    ('warriors-battle-cards-mission-brief', 'craft-statement-of-desire', $body$Write the mission with measurable specificity, set the deadline, state the price of victory, and connect the goal to a deep personal why.

The finished declaration becomes part of the Mission Brief and should be read daily as an anchor for belief, focus, and execution.$body$),
    ('warriors-battle-cards-mission-brief', 'daily-execution-commitment', $body$Your Mission Brief only works if it becomes part of the day. Decide where it will live, when you will review it, and how you will use it to reset attention.

The goal is not inspiration alone. The goal is daily visibility that drives daily action.$body$),

    ('warriors-mission-defining-your-purpose', 'what-is-mission-statement', $body$A mission statement is your personal battle plan: a clear declaration of what you stand for, how you act, and the path you are committed to walking daily.

Vision is the long-range future you are building. Mission is the daily code of conduct and execution plan that brings that future to life.$body$),
    ('warriors-mission-defining-your-purpose', 'mission-vs-vision', $body$Vision describes the destination. Mission describes how you live on the way there. Vision gives direction; mission governs daily decisions.

When doubt, fear, and setbacks appear, your mission statement becomes the compass that keeps action aligned with purpose.$body$),
    ('warriors-mission-defining-your-purpose', 'discover-your-mission', $body$Your mission is built from values, strengths, and passions. Values define what you refuse to compromise. Strengths reveal how you create value. Passions show where energy and meaning naturally gather.

Capture these inputs honestly. They form the raw material of your Warrior Profile and your final mission statement.$body$),
    ('warriors-mission-defining-your-purpose', 'craft-mission-statement', $body$A strong mission statement is clear, powerful, and personal. It identifies what you are committed to achieving, how you will achieve it, and which values govern your behavior.

Use the template to define purpose, integrate values, and name the impact beyond personal success.$body$),
    ('warriors-mission-defining-your-purpose', 'mission-brief-declaration', $body$The MISSION Brief Declaration captures the goal, category, deadline, sacrifice, plan of attack, oath, and accountability person.

It connects purpose to a specific target and turns the mission into a signed operating commitment.$body$),
    ('warriors-mission-defining-your-purpose', 'living-your-mission', $body$A mission statement must move from writing exercise to identity practice. Review it consistently until it becomes an internal compass that shapes decisions, habits, and execution.

Repetition matters. What you review daily begins to govern what you choose under pressure.$body$),
    ('warriors-mission-defining-your-purpose', '30-day-warrior-commitment', $body$The 30-day Warrior Commitment embeds the mission through repetition. Read it in the morning, revisit it midday, and speak it at night before reflection.

Track the practice for 30 days. The aim is subconscious conditioning through repeated declaration and action.$body$),
    ('warriors-mission-defining-your-purpose', 'daily-alignment-reflection', $body$Evening reflection keeps the mission honest. Review where your actions aligned, where you drifted, and what must change tomorrow.

The point is not guilt. The point is correction and realignment before drift becomes a pattern.$body$),
    ('warriors-mission-defining-your-purpose', 'recap-reflection', $body$Your mission should now be clear enough to guide decisions and strong enough to challenge compromise.

Compare it with the vision from Module 1. If the two do not align, refine the wording until your mission serves the future you are building.$body$),

    ('tactical-goal-setting-breaking-down-the-mission', 'begin-with-end', $body$Begin with the end in mind. Long-range planning starts by defining what victory looks like across the WARRIOR framework: health, habits, wealth, relationships, identity, work, and resolve.

The goal is not vague ambition. The goal is a balanced 15-year vision made of specific, measurable, inspiring targets.$body$),
    ('tactical-goal-setting-breaking-down-the-mission', '15-year-warrior-vision', $body$Build your 15-year WARRIOR vision by naming at least one ambitious goal in each category. These are long-range Big Dominos that create positive ripple effects across life.

Think bigger than short-term comfort. Define the future with enough clarity that you can work backward from it.$body$),
    ('tactical-goal-setting-breaking-down-the-mission', 'working-backward-milestones', $body$A 15-year vision becomes executable when you work backward. Break long-term goals into 10-year, 7-year, 5-year, 3-year, and 1-year milestones.

Each milestone is a checkpoint for progress, strategy adjustment, and renewed alignment with mission.$body$),
    ('tactical-goal-setting-breaking-down-the-mission', 'monthly-battle-plans', $body$Monthly battle plans define the current warpath. They translate long-range milestones into near-term objectives that can be reviewed and adjusted.

Choose category goals, primary objectives, and success measures for the month so effort has a clear target.$body$),
    ('tactical-goal-setting-breaking-down-the-mission', 'weekly-battle-plans', $body$Weekly plans create marching orders. They identify what must move this week, which WARRIOR category it supports, and which actions deserve priority.

A strong week is designed before it begins. Do not let urgency write the plan for you.$body$),
    ('tactical-goal-setting-breaking-down-the-mission', 'daily-strikes', $body$Daily strikes turn weekly plans into action. Each day needs specific movements that create progress, not just activity.

Use the daily log to capture what was done, visualize the target, and mark completion. Small strikes compound into major victories.$body$),
    ('tactical-goal-setting-breaking-down-the-mission', 'hourly-planner', $body$The hourly planner protects execution time. Block the actions that matter before low-value tasks consume the day.

Time blocks make the plan visible and reduce the decision fatigue that leads to drift.$body$),
    ('tactical-goal-setting-breaking-down-the-mission', 'big-dominos', $body$Review the goals and actions with the biggest ripple effect. These Big Dominos should receive the best time, energy, and attention.

If everything is treated as equal, the mission loses force. Prioritize what moves the most.$body$),
    ('tactical-goal-setting-breaking-down-the-mission', 'celebrate-victory', $body$Progress should be acknowledged deliberately. Celebrating small wins strengthens motivation, reinforces discipline, and reminds you that daily victories compound.

Record completed milestones and name how each win supports the mission.$body$),
    ('tactical-goal-setting-breaking-down-the-mission', 'final-warrior-reflection', $body$Planning must end in action. Identify the top three actions you will take today and the discipline you must double down on.

The plan is only complete when it changes what you do next.$body$),

    ('mastering-time-warriors-command-over-his-day', 'time-domination-overview', $body$Time mastery starts with priority mastery. The warrior identifies the day's Most Important Task, attacks it first, and stops letting messages, emails, and minor obligations dictate the day.

You are not given more hours than other men. You must use the hours differently.$body$),
    ('mastering-time-warriors-command-over-his-day', 'power-of-prioritization', $body$Prioritization means naming the action that matters most before the day begins. The most important task should be attacked before distractions take command.

Choose today's frog and commit to doing it first. Momentum starts when the highest-value action is no longer negotiable.$body$),
    ('mastering-time-warriors-command-over-his-day', '8020-vital-few', $body$The 80/20 Rule asks which small set of actions creates most of the results. Not every task deserves equal attention.

List current projects and tasks, identify the vital few, and decide what to eliminate, automate, or delegate.$body$),
    ('mastering-time-warriors-command-over-his-day', 'high-low-value-tasks', $body$High-value tasks directly advance the mission. Low-value tasks create motion without meaningful progress.

Define the top five high-value tasks for the week and schedule them before lesser obligations consume the calendar.$body$),
    ('mastering-time-warriors-command-over-his-day', 'time-thieves', $body$No protects the mission. Time thieves often appear as unnecessary meetings, social media, phone distractions, disorganized workspaces, and commitments accepted out of habit.

Name where you say yes too often. Then write the boundaries that will protect focus.$body$),
    ('mastering-time-warriors-command-over-his-day', 'eisenhower-matrix', $body$The Eisenhower Matrix separates urgent from important. Quadrant 1 is urgent and important. Quadrant 2 is important but not urgent. Quadrant 3 is urgent but not important. Quadrant 4 is neither.

Spend more time in Quadrant 2: planning, training, relationships, spiritual growth, and strategic work. The more you live there, the fewer crises control you.$body$),
    ('mastering-time-warriors-command-over-his-day', 'task-scoring-tool', $body$Task scoring forces an honest decision. Score each task by duration and impact, then choose whether to Do, Delegate, Date, or Dump it.

The goal is not to manage an endless task list. The goal is to make better decisions about where attention belongs.$body$),

    ('peak-performance-training-for-maximum-impact', 'peak-performance-overview', $body$High performance is sustained, strategic execution toward meaningful goals without burnout. It is not constant hustle. It is disciplined action supported by clarity, energy, purpose, and strong systems.

This module trains the conditions that allow execution to stay consistent.$body$),
    ('peak-performance-training-for-maximum-impact', 'what-is-high-performance', $body$High performers consistently achieve meaningful goals, maintain clarity and focus, manage energy, and connect work to purpose.

Define your biggest goals, evaluate your current performance, and choose one change this week that would raise the standard.$body$),
    ('peak-performance-training-for-maximum-impact', 'four-pillars', $body$Peak performance has four connected pillars: Productivity, Persuasion, Physiology, and Psychology.

Productivity is strategic execution. Persuasion is influence and leadership. Physiology is physical energy and resilience. Psychology is mindset, focus, and confidence.$body$),
    ('peak-performance-training-for-maximum-impact', 'productivity', $body$Productivity is not busyness. It is strategic execution of the actions that matter most.

Set clear goals, protect deep work, and attack the hardest task first. The day should be built around meaningful progress.$body$),
    ('peak-performance-training-for-maximum-impact', 'persuasion', $body$Persuasion is influence rooted in clarity, integrity, and relationship. Strong communication helps you lead, sell, negotiate, and build trust.

Review recent conversations and identify where clarity, empathy, or decisive language could improve.$body$),
    ('peak-performance-training-for-maximum-impact', 'physiology', $body$Your body is part of the operating system. Exercise, nutrition, sleep, and hydration determine the energy available for execution.

Assess where the body is supporting the mission and where it is limiting performance. Choose one health action for the week.$body$),
    ('peak-performance-training-for-maximum-impact', 'psychology', $body$Psychology governs emotional control, confidence, resilience, and focus. A strong mindset does not deny challenge; it chooses response and action.

Reflect on a recent challenge and identify one mental habit that would have made you stronger in it.$body$),
    ('peak-performance-training-for-maximum-impact', 'morning-routine', $body$Morning routines create momentum before the day becomes reactive. Use reflection or prayer, movement, affirmations, visualization, and priority review to start with command.

Build a routine you can repeat consistently rather than an ideal routine you abandon.$body$),
    ('peak-performance-training-for-maximum-impact', 'evening-routine', $body$Evening routines close the loop. Review the day, practice gratitude, set tomorrow's top priority, and reset the environment.

The next day begins before sleep. End with strategy instead of drift.$body$),

    ('warriors-daily-system-consistency-and-execution', 'battle-report-overview', $body$The Battle Report is the heart of the Warrior's daily system. It brings goals, habits, priorities, and reflections into one recurring routine that drives momentum.

The system trains consistency. Each morning sets the mission; each evening extracts lessons; each week resets the plan.$body$),
    ('warriors-daily-system-consistency-and-execution', 'weekly-planning', $body$Weekly planning sets the tone before the week begins. Review your goals, identify the key targets, and define the priorities that deserve attention.

The weekly plan should align with long-range goals from earlier modules. It gives each day a clear battlefield.$body$),
    ('warriors-daily-system-consistency-and-execution', 'warrior-check-in', $body$The WARRIOR check-in is a visual assessment of focus across the major areas of life. It helps you notice which areas are strong, which are neglected, and where the week needs attention.

Use the ratings to choose focus, not to judge yourself. The point is correction.$body$),
    ('warriors-daily-system-consistency-and-execution', 'morning-setup', $body$Every morning you choose whether to drift or attack the day with purpose. The Battle Report primes your mind and body for battle before distractions arrive.

Track sleep and energy, review WARRIOR goals, reinforce habit streaks, and identify the Top 3 mission priorities for the day.$body$),
    ('warriors-daily-system-consistency-and-execution', 'habit-streaks', $body$Great warriors do not rely on motivation. They build unbreakable habits. Track the top four habits that support your mission and protect the streak.

If you complete the habit, the streak continues. If you miss, reset honestly and rebuild immediately.$body$),
    ('warriors-daily-system-consistency-and-execution', 'evening-reflection', $body$A warrior does not just fight; he analyzes, refines, and improves. The evening reflection extracts wisdom from the day's battles.

Record what happened, what needs follow-up, what you learned, what you are grateful for, and how much time you invested in growth.$body$),
    ('warriors-daily-system-consistency-and-execution', 'weekly-reset', $body$The weekly reset is the general's strategy session. Review the Battle Reports from the past week, identify victories and weaknesses, and set the next week's priorities.

Adapt without abandoning the mission. Small refinements create massive long-term improvement.$body$),
    ('warriors-daily-system-consistency-and-execution', 'warrior-score', $body$The Warrior Score captures execution quality and gives the week a measurable review point.

The exact automated formula still needs final confirmation, but the discipline is clear: score execution, learn from the pattern, and adjust the next week.$body$),

    ('code-of-discipline-rituals-of-success', 'discipline-overview', $body$Success is built in unseen hours through small daily disciplines that create unstoppable momentum. The difference between men who rise and men who stall is not talent or luck; it is discipline.

Every day you train yourself. You either reinforce habits that make you stronger or indulge habits that make you weaker.$body$),
    ('code-of-discipline-rituals-of-success', '10-daily-disciplines', $body$The ten daily disciplines are weapons for sharpening the mind, strengthening the body, and solidifying the mission: affirm and visualize, practice gratitude, read and learn, train and hydrate, take micro-breaks, set daily targets, trust instincts, show appreciation, plan tomorrow today, and review wins.

These are not optional habits. They create the daily code that keeps execution alive when motivation fades.$body$),
    ('code-of-discipline-rituals-of-success', 'affirm-visualize', $body$Your mind is the first battlefield of the day. Speak your warrior statement out loud and visualize yourself completing the mission.

This primes the subconscious and locks attention onto victory before distraction can take hold.$body$),
    ('code-of-discipline-rituals-of-success', 'gratitude', $body$A warrior does not focus on what he lacks. Gratitude trains attention toward strength, opportunity, and responsibility.

Write three things you are grateful for and use them to replace entitlement, negativity, and distraction.$body$),
    ('code-of-discipline-rituals-of-success', 'read-learn', $body$A warrior who does not train his mind loses his edge. Read, study, and refine your skills every day.

Knowledge compounds. Who you become is shaped by what you consume and apply.$body$),
    ('code-of-discipline-rituals-of-success', 'train-hydrate', $body$Your physical state affects energy, focus, and execution. Train the body, hydrate deliberately, and treat health as part of the mission.

The body is the machine that carries the plan. Treat it like a weapon.$body$),
    ('code-of-discipline-rituals-of-success', 'daily-targets', $body$A warrior does not enter battle without a strategy. Define the three critical actions that make the day successful.

Focus on execution, not busy work. Most people stay busy; warriors stay effective.$body$),
    ('code-of-discipline-rituals-of-success', 'review-celebrate', $body$A warrior who does not review his battles does not improve. End the day by recording what was accomplished, what was learned, and what win deserves recognition.

Tracking wins builds momentum and confidence.$body$),

    ('warriors-creed-programming-mindset-of-victory', 'mindset-victory-overview', $body$Words are weapons. What you speak, you reinforce; what you reinforce becomes part of your reality.

A warrior does not allow doubt, weakness, or negativity to take root. He trains his mind daily with intentional declarations aligned to the life he is building.$body$),
    ('warriors-creed-programming-mindset-of-victory', 'power-of-affirmations', $body$Affirmations are declarations of intent: commands to the subconscious to align actions with identity and mission.

Used daily, they embed certainty, discipline, and focus. They do not replace action; they condition the mind to execute.$body$),
    ('warriors-creed-programming-mindset-of-victory', 'powerful-affirmation', $body$A powerful affirmation is present tense, positive, personal, and tied to action. Speak as if you are becoming the man required for the mission.

Weak statements describe wishes. Warrior statements command identity, behavior, and standards.$body$),
    ('warriors-creed-programming-mindset-of-victory', 'affirmation-library', $body$Use the affirmation library as raw material for your own declarations. Categories include identity, relationships, occupation, spirituality, physical health, emotional mastery, and financial resources.

Select what resonates, then adapt the language until it feels personal, direct, and actionable.$body$),
    ('warriors-creed-programming-mindset-of-victory', 'craft-warriors-creed', $body$Your Warrior's Creed should align with your goals, values, and mission. Identify the life areas that matter, define the goal in each, and turn the goal into a victory statement.

Use strong, decisive language that creates emotion and action. The final creed should be something you can read daily without hesitation.$body$),
    ('warriors-creed-programming-mindset-of-victory', 'daily-practice', $body$Read your creed aloud in the morning to set your mental state. Read it again before bed to program the subconscious as you sleep.

As you say the words, visualize yourself living them. Repetition becomes belief, belief becomes action, and action becomes reality.$body$),
    ('warriors-creed-programming-mindset-of-victory', '30-day-creed-challenge', $body$For 30 days, read the creed every morning and every night. Track completion, confidence, mindset impact, and execution.

The challenge is designed to prove that language, visualization, and repetition can shift behavior when practiced consistently.$body$),
    ('warriors-creed-programming-mindset-of-victory', 'final-creed-reflection', $body$Review the change created by the creed practice. What shifted in confidence, behavior, standards, or focus?

The words you repeat become the man you become. Speak it, live it, and keep refining the creed as your mission grows.$body$)
)
update public.sections as s
set content = jsonb_set(coalesce(s.content, '{}'::jsonb), '{body}', to_jsonb(content_updates.body), true)
from public.chapters as c, public.modules as m, content_updates
where s.chapter_id = c.id
  and c.module_id = m.id
  and m.slug = content_updates.module_slug
  and s.slug = content_updates.section_slug;
